fields.description:
The JavaDoc for testCollationService.collateTestResults says:
{code}
Collates {@link TestClassResult}s and {@link TestCaseResult}s from {@link TaskContext#getWorkingDirectory()} using the specified file pattern
{code}

However, the code for TestCollationServiceImpl.collateTestResults says:
{code}
...
    final File sourceDirectory = taskContext.getRootDirectory();
...
{code}

(Checked in source code of 5.1.1)

Kindly fix one or the other :-)

e.g. 
{code}
http://localhost:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/queue/WOO-LONG-7
{code}
and 
{code}
http://localhost:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/queue/WOO-LONG-7
{code}
The current errors are that "The specified HTTP method is not allowed for the requested resource."

There are two problems
* Currently there are conflicting endpoints.  The pattern differences between the PUT and DELETE endpoints cause them to create different matching rules, and the above urls match both, unfortunately it is the PUT endpoint which ends up trying to resolve the request.
* Even when resolving the above issue this rest end point does not work as expected.  Passing a job key will not match the pattern expected and the request will be rejected.  Passing a plan key will match and tell you it worked, but actually did nothing.

If a user tries to directly access artifacts (eg https://extranet-bamboo.internal.atlassian.com/browse/CRUCHG-DEFAULT-1161/artifact/shared/FishEye-Zip---Deployment-Artifacts/ ) as an unauthenticated user they receive the following browser message:

{noformat}
Forbidden

Unable to access this resource. The maximum number of failed login attempts may have been reached. Please log into the web application through the web interface to reset the number of failed login attempts.
{noformat}

This causes confusion & friction for the user. They then need to log in, and then come back to the original link, and force-refresh of the browser page to then obtain access to the artifact directory
